  • ⇒ Actual Weight: is exactly what the product weighs including packaging.

  • ⇒ Volumetric Weight: Volumetric weight is calculated by multiplying the length x height x width of a package and dividing the result by a volumetric factor.

  • ⇒ Billable Weight: is defined as the greater of the two weights (Actual vs. Volumetric) and this will be used to calculate the shipment cost.
